Subject: Lecture "Game Design:" Dr. Reiner Knizia; Tuesday 20 April



**Playmakers Lecture**


	Dr. Reiner Knizia

	Game Design


	Tuesday 20 April

	4:00pm

	Bartos Theatre, Wiesner Building (E15)


Are you curious about what it takes to create a really engaging game?
Let Dr. Reiner Knizia, game designer, take you from the initial idea
all the way to a game's market release. Learn what makes a good game,
what makes a successful game, and what makes a successful game
designer. Dr. Knizia will speak about game design philosophies, new
trends and specific examples, all with a particular focus on the
differences between Europe and the USA.


BIO

---

Dr. Reiner Knizia is one of Europe's most prolific and successful game

designers.  He has designed over 100 games, written a number of books

on games, won the Deutscher Spielepreis (German Game Prize) twice, in
1993 for <italic>Modern Art</italic> and 1998 for <italic>Euphrates &
Tigris, </italic>and been a six time nominee for the Spiel des Jahres
(Game of the Year). He won Children's Game of the Year in Finland in
1998 for <italic>Kurre</italic>, and the Golden Quill of Essen in 1994
for the book <italic>New Games in Old Rome</italic>. 


Born in 1957 in Germany. Dr. Knizia has a Diploma in Mathematics
(University of Ulm, Germany), a Master of Science (Syracuse University,
USA), and a PHD in Mathematics (University of Ulm). He is the Senior
Project Manager for Software Development, Deputy Area Director of
Information Technology, and Area Director of Strategic Planning in a
large financial institution in Germany, and General Manager and
Director of a large mortgage company in the United Kingdom. In
addition, he has teaching assignments at various universities and the
ABECOR Banking Institute, mainly on Management and Project Management.


(About Euphrat & Tigris) "brilliant work..." 

